So as we found out a couple of weeks ago, she hasn't been too happy with the ratty clothes I've been making for her. And she decided to go hunting online for her own clothes. Luckily for us, she found @leanakonovalova.doll.clothes on @etsy, who sews impeccable tiny clothes, something that I personally find amazing because I'm really bad at sewing at that scale.

Striking deals with the devil is always a questionable idea. But hey, when has that ever stopped anyone? Head over to my profile @ruchikanambiar to see what happens next! • 
CREDITS (These will make more sense once you've seen Part 2 of the story)
A special thank you to @manushjohn : His impeccable digital sculpting expertise (i.e. he sculpted a digital model of my face which we then 3D printed) made this storyline possible far sooner than I'd imagined. •
Thanks also to the capitalist machinery of the 21st century, for finally deciding it was profitable to produce seamless silicone dolls in the 1/12 scale.
•
And finally a moment of silence, in memory of Doll 1.0.2 and her tireless contributions to this project. She braved a great many feats (including exposure to an actual showerhead) and she will be missed. May she rest in peace. In a box. In my drawer. •
You'll be seeing a lot more of Doll 2.0 over the next many weeks. And stay tuned for a proper #behindthescenes Doll Evolution video coming soon where you'll also see @manushjohn's head sculpting process! •
Music credit: purple-planet.com
